Detailed Description

Crack propagation data and methods

  • Functions strarting with build, for example buildElastic, add and build fields.
  • Functions starting with declare, for example declareElasticFE, add and build finite elements.
  • Functions starting with assemble, for example assembleElasticDM, create finite element instances and operators.
  • Functions starting with create, for example createElasticDM, create problems.

Constructor of Crack Propagation, prints fracture module version and registers the three interfaces used to solve fracture problem, i.e. CrackPropagation, CPSolvers and CPMeshCut.

Parameters
m_fieldinterface to MoAB database
approx_orderorder of approximation space, default is 2
geometry_orderorder of geometry, default is 1 (can be up to 2)

4183 new HookeElement::OpCalculateStress<1>("SPATIAL_POSITION",
4184 "SPATIAL_POSITION",
4185 data_hooke_element_at_pts));
4186
4187 feLhs->getOpPtrVector().push_back(new OpTransfromSingularBaseFunctions(
4188 feLhs->singularElement, feLhs->detS, feLhs->invSJac));
4189 feLhs->getOpPtrVector().push_back(new HookeElement::OpAleLhs_dx_dx<1>(
4190 "SPATIAL_POSITION", "SPATIAL_POSITION", data_hooke_element_at_pts));
4191
4192 } else {
4193 feLhs->getOpPtrVector().push_back(
4194 new HookeElement::OpCalculateHomogeneousStiffness<0>(
4195 "SPATIAL_POSITION", "SPATIAL_POSITION", block_sets_ptr,
4196 data_hooke_element_at_pts));
4197 // Calculate spatial positions and gradients (of deformation) at
4198 // integration pts. This operator takes into account singularity at
4199 // crack front
4200 feLhs->getOpPtrVector().push_back(
4201 new OpGetCrackFrontDataGradientAtGaussPts(
4202 "SPATIAL_POSITION", data_hooke_element_at_pts->hMat,
4203 feLhs->singularElement, feLhs->invSJac));
4204 feLhs->getOpPtrVector().push_back(
4205 new HookeElement::OpCalculateStrainAle("SPATIAL_POSITION",
4206 "SPATIAL_POSITION",
4207 data_hooke_element_at_pts));
4208 feLhs->getOpPtrVector().push_back(
4209 new HookeElement::OpCalculateStress<0>("SPATIAL_POSITION",
4210 "SPATIAL_POSITION",
4211 data_hooke_element_at_pts));
4212 // Transform base functions to get singular base functions at crack
4213 // front
4214 feLhs->getOpPtrVector().push_back(new OpTransfromSingularBaseFunctions(
4215 feLhs->singularElement, feLhs->detS, feLhs->invSJac));
4216 feLhs->getOpPtrVector().push_back(new HookeElement::OpAleLhs_dx_dx<0>(
4217 "SPATIAL_POSITION", "SPATIAL_POSITION", data_hooke_element_at_pts));
4218 }

1607 bit, mask, MBTET, proc_ents);
1608 map<int, Range> layers;
1609 Range ref_nodes = crackFrontNodes;
1610 for (int ll = 0; ll != refOrderAtTip; ll++) {
1611 Range tets;
1612 CHKERR moab.get_adjacencies(ref_nodes, 3, false, tets,
1613 moab::Interface::UNION);
1614 tets = intersect(tets_level_all, tets);
1615 layers[ll] = tets;
1616 Range ref_order_ents;
1617 CHKERR moab.get_adjacencies(tets, 2, false, ref_order_ents,
1618 moab::Interface::UNION);
1619 CHKERR moab.get_adjacencies(tets, 1, false, ref_order_ents,
1620 moab::Interface::UNION);
1621 layers[ll].merge(ref_order_ents);
1622 CHKERR moab.get_connectivity(tets, ref_nodes, false);
1623
1624 if (!contact_faces.empty()) {
1625 Range contact_layer = intersect(layers[ll], contact_faces);
1626 for (Range::iterator tit = contact_layer.begin();
1627 tit != contact_layer.end(); tit++) {
1628 Range contact_prisms, contact_tris;
1629 CHKERR moab.get_adjacencies(&*tit, 1, 3, false, contact_prisms,
1630 moab::Interface::UNION);
1631 contact_prisms = contact_prisms.subset_by_type(MBPRISM);
1632
1633 Range contact_elements;
1634 if (!contactElements.empty() || !mortarContactElements.empty()) {
1635 contact_elements.merge(contactElements);
1636 contact_elements.merge(mortarContactElements);
1637 contact_elements = intersect(contact_prisms, contact_elements);
1638 if (contact_elements.empty()) {
1639 SETERRQ(PETSC_COMM_SELF, MOFEM_DATA_INCONSISTENCY,
1640 "Expecting adjacent contact prism(s), but none found");
1641 }
1642 CHKERR moab.get_adjacencies(contact_elements, 2, false,
1643 contact_tris, moab::Interface::UNION);
1644 contact_tris = contact_tris.subset_by_type(MBTRI);
1645 if (contact_tris.size() < 2) {
1646 SETERRQ1(
1647 PETSC_COMM_SELF, MOFEM_DATA_INCONSISTENCY,
1648 "Expecting 2 or more adjacent contact tris, but %d found",
1649 contact_tris.size());
1650 }
1651 }
1652
1653 layers[ll].merge(contact_tris);
1654 Range contact_edges, contact_nodes;
1655 CHKERR moab.get_adjacencies(contact_tris, 1, false, contact_edges,
1656 moab::Interface::UNION);
1657 layers[ll].merge(contact_edges);
1658 CHKERR moab.get_connectivity(contact_tris, contact_nodes, false);
1659 ref_nodes.merge(contact_nodes);
1660 }
1661 }
1662 }
1663 int poo = 1;
1664 for (map<int, Range>::reverse_iterator mit = layers.rbegin();
1665 mit != layers.rend(); mit++, poo++) {
1666 mit->second = intersect(mit->second, dofs_ents);
1667 CHKERR mField.set_field_order(mit->second, "SPATIAL_POSITION",
1668 approxOrder + poo, verb);
1669 non_ref_ents = subtract(non_ref_ents, mit->second);
1670
1671 if (debug) {
1672 CHKERR write_file("layer_order_" + std::to_string(approxOrder + poo) +
1673 ".vtk",
1674 mit->second);
1675 }
1676 }
1677 }
1678
1679 if (!contactElements.empty() || !mortarContactElements.empty()) {
1680 if (contactOrder > approxOrder) {
1681 Range cont_ents, cont_adj_ent;
1682 cont_ents.merge(contactSlaveFaces);
1683 cont_ents.merge(contactMasterFaces);
1684 cont_ents.merge(mortarContactMasterFaces);
1685 cont_ents.merge(mortarContactSlaveFaces);
1686
1687 CHKERR moab.get_adjacencies(cont_ents, 1, false, cont_adj_ent,
1688 moab::Interface::UNION);
1689 cont_ents.merge(cont_adj_ent);
1690 cont_ents = intersect(cont_ents, non_ref_ents);
1691 CHKERR mField.set_field_order(cont_ents, "SPATIAL_POSITION", contactOrder,
1692 verb);
1693 if (debug) {
1694 CHKERR write_file("contact_order_" + std::to_string(contactOrder) +
1695 ".vtk",
1696 cont_ents);
1697 }
1698 }
1699
1700 // add Lagrange multipliers field for contact constraints on slave faces
1701 CHKERR mField.add_field("LAMBDA_CONTACT", H1, AINSWORTH_LEGENDRE_BASE, 1,
1702 MB_TAG_SPARSE, MF_ZERO);
1703
1704 if (!contactSlaveFaces.empty())
1705 CHKERR mField.add_ents_to_field_by_type(contactSlaveFaces, MBTRI,
1706 "LAMBDA_CONTACT");
1707
1708 if (!mortarContactSlaveFaces.empty())
1709 CHKERR mField.add_ents_to_field_by_type(mortarContactSlaveFaces, MBTRI,
1710 "LAMBDA_CONTACT");
1711
1712 CHKERR mField.set_field_order(0, MBTRI, "LAMBDA_CONTACT",
1713 contactLambdaOrder);
1714 CHKERR mField.set_field_order(0, MBEDGE, "LAMBDA_CONTACT",
1715 contactLambdaOrder);
1716 CHKERR mField.set_field_order(0, MBVERTEX, "LAMBDA_CONTACT", 1);
1717 }
1718
1719 CHKERR mField.build_fields(verb);
1720
1721 MoFEMFunctionReturn(0);
1722}

7406 feEnergy->eNergy);
7407 } else {

7409 feEnergy->eNergy);

8321 auto calculate_diagonal_scale = [&]() {
8322 MoFEMFunctionBegin;
8323
8324 SmartPetscObj<Vec> f = smartVectorDuplicate(q);
8325 CHKERR SnesRhs(snes, q, f, arc_snes_ctx);
8326
8327 const double *f_array;
8328 CHKERR VecGetArrayRead(f, &f_array);
8329 auto &rows_index =
8330 problem_ptr->getNumeredRowDofsPtr()->get<Unique_mi_tag>();
8331 const int nb_local = problem_ptr->getNbLocalDofsRow();
8332
8333 constexpr size_t nb_fields = 2;
8334 std::array<std::string, nb_fields> fields = {"SPATIAL_POSITION",
8335 "LAMBDA_CLOSE_CRACK"};
8336 std::array<double, nb_fields> lnorms = {0, 0};
8337 std::array<double, nb_fields> norms = {0, 0};
8338 std::array<double, nb_fields> loc_nb_dofs = {0, 0};
8339 std::array<double, nb_fields> glob_nb_dofs = {0, 0};
8340
8341 int nb = mField.check_field("LAMBDA_CLOSE_CRACK") ? nb_fields : 1;
8342
8343 for (size_t f = 0; f != nb; ++f) {
8344 const auto bit_number = mField.get_field_bit_number(fields[f]);
8345 const auto lo_uid =
8346 rows_index.lower_bound(FieldEntity::getLoBitNumberUId(bit_number));
8347 const auto hi_uid =
8348 rows_index.upper_bound(FieldEntity::getHiBitNumberUId(bit_number));
8349 for (auto lo = lo_uid; lo != hi_uid; ++lo) {
8350 const int local_idx = (*lo)->getPetscLocalDofIdx();
8351 if (local_idx >= 0 && local_idx < nb_local) {
8352 const double val = f_array[local_idx];
8353 lnorms[f] += val * val;
8354 ++loc_nb_dofs[f];
8355 }
8356 }
8357 }
8358
8359 CHKERR VecRestoreArrayRead(f, &f_array);
8360 CHKERR MPIU_Allreduce(lnorms.data(), norms.data(), nb, MPIU_REAL, MPIU_SUM,
8361 PetscObjectComm((PetscObject)dm));
8362 CHKERR MPIU_Allreduce(loc_nb_dofs.data(), glob_nb_dofs.data(), nb,
8363 MPIU_REAL, MPIU_SUM,
8364 PetscObjectComm((PetscObject)dm));
8365
8366 for (auto &v : norms)
8367 v = sqrt(v);
8368
8369 for (size_t f = 0; f != nb; ++f)
8370 MOFEM_LOG_C("CPWorld", Sev::verbose,
8371 "Scaling diaginal for field [ %s ] by %9.8e nb. of dofs %d",
8372 fields[f].c_str(), norms[f],
8373 static_cast<double>(glob_nb_dofs[f]));
8374
8375 CHKERR VecSet(arc_snes_ctx->getVecDiagM(), 1.);
8376 double *diag_m_array;
8377 CHKERR VecGetArray(arc_snes_ctx->getVecDiagM(), &diag_m_array);
8378
8379 for (size_t f = 0; f != nb; ++f) {
8380 if (norms[f] > 0) {
8381 const auto bit_number = mField.get_field_bit_number(fields[f]);
8382 const auto lo_uid = FieldEntity::getLoBitNumberUId(bit_number);
8383 const auto hi_uid = FieldEntity::getHiBitNumberUId(bit_number);
8384 for (auto lo = rows_index.lower_bound(lo_uid);
8385 lo != rows_index.upper_bound(hi_uid); ++lo) {
8386 const int local_idx = (*lo)->getPetscLocalDofIdx();
8387 if (local_idx >= 0 && local_idx < nb_local)
8388 diag_m_array[local_idx] = 1. / norms[f];
8389 }
8390 }
8391 }
8392
8393 CHKERR VecGetArray(arc_snes_ctx->getVecDiagM(), &diag_m_array);
8394
8395 MoFEMFunctionReturn(0);
8396 };

8772 bool contain = ents->find((*lo)->getEnt()) != ents->end();
8773 if (not_contain) {
8774 if (contain)
8775 no_skip = false;
8776 } else {
8777 if (!contain)
8778 no_skip = false;
8779 }
8780 }
8781
8782 if (no_skip) {
8783 const double val = v_array[local_idx];
8784 ret_val += val * val;
8785 ++size;
8786 }
8787 }
8788 }
8789 CHKERR VecRestoreArrayRead(vec, &v_array);
8790 return std::pair<double, double>(ret_val, size);
8791 };

8793 auto set_norm_from_vec = [&](Vec vec, std::string field, const double norm,
8794 Range *ents, bool not_contain) {
8795 MoFEMFunctionBegin;
8796
8797 if (!std::isnormal(norm))
8798 SETERRQ(PETSC_COMM_SELF, MOFEM_DATA_INCONSISTENCY,
8799 "Wrong scaling value");
8800
8801 double *v_array;
8802 CHKERR VecGetArray(vec, &v_array);
8803
8804 const auto bit_number = mField.get_field_bit_number(field);
8805 const auto lo_uid = FieldEntity::getLoBitNumberUId(bit_number);
8806 const auto hi_uid = FieldEntity::getHiBitNumberUId(bit_number);
8807
8808 for (auto lo = rows_index.lower_bound(lo_uid);
8809 lo != rows_index.upper_bound(hi_uid); ++lo) {
8810
8811 const int local_idx = (*lo)->getPetscLocalDofIdx();
8812 if (local_idx >= 0 && local_idx < nb_local) {
8813
8814 bool no_skip = true;
8815 if (ents) {
8816 bool contain = ents->find((*lo)->getEnt()) != ents->end();
8817 if (not_contain) {
8818 if (contain)
8819 no_skip = false;
8820 } else {
8821 if (!contain)
8822 no_skip = false;
8823 }
8824 }
8825
8826 if (no_skip)
8827 v_array[local_idx] /= norm;
8828 }
8829 }
8830 CHKERR VecRestoreArray(vec, &v_array);
8831 MoFEMFunctionReturn(0);
8832 };

8834 auto calulate_norms = [&](auto &lnorms, auto &lsizes, auto &norms,
8835 auto &sizes) {
8836 MoFEMFunctionBegin;
8837 const double lambda = arc_snes_ctx->getArcPtr()->getFieldData();
8838 std::pair<double &, double &>(lnorms[0], lsizes[0]) =
8839 get_norm_from_vec(f, "LAMBDA_ARC_LENGTH", nullptr, false);
8840 std::pair<double &, double &>(lnorms[1], lsizes[1]) =
8841 get_norm_from_vec(f_lambda, "SPATIAL_POSITION", nullptr, false);
8842 std::pair<double &, double &>(lnorms[2], lsizes[2]) = get_norm_from_vec(
8843 f_griffith, "MESH_NODE_POSITIONS", &crackFrontNodes, false);
8844 std::pair<double &, double &>(lnorms[3], lsizes[3]) = get_norm_from_vec(
8845 diag_griffith, "MESH_NODE_POSITIONS", &crackFrontNodes, false);
8846 std::pair<double &, double &>(lnorms[4], lsizes[4]) = get_norm_from_vec(
8847 diag_smoothing, "MESH_NODE_POSITIONS", &crackFrontNodes, false);
8848
8849 CHKERR MPIU_Allreduce(lnorms.data(), norms.data(), lnorms.size(),
8850 MPIU_REAL, MPIU_SUM,
8851 PetscObjectComm((PetscObject)dm));
8852 CHKERR MPIU_Allreduce(lsizes.data(), sizes.data(), lnorms.size(),
8853 MPIU_REAL, MPIU_SUM,
8854 PetscObjectComm((PetscObject)dm));
8855
8856 for (auto &v : norms)
8857 v = sqrt(v);
8858
8859 norms[1] *= lambda;
8860 norms[3] /= norms[1];
8861 norms[4] /= norms[1];
8862 norms[3] /= sizes[3];
8863 norms[4] /= sizes[4];
8864
8865 MoFEMFunctionReturn(0);
8866 };
